name: Hu tieu go ne
description: When making this track, the knocking sound (gõ) reminded me of hủ tiếu gõ street food vendor. In the old days, a boy would walk or bike 🚲 around the neighborhood while knocking an empty bowl to get the orders for hủ tiếu. Actually, hủ tiếu is originally from Cambodia 🇰🇭, called Kuy Teav, made popular by Chinese vendors and enjoyed by local diners.
